-- Eptisa Awarded Water Infrastructure Project in Romanian County
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-11-02T11:24:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-02/eptisa-awarded-water-infrastructure-project-in-romanian-county.html
Eptisa has been awarded a water
infrastructure contract in  Romania  to rehabilitate and upgrade
the potable water supplies and sewage treatment capacity in
Caras Severin County, the group said.  The project contract from the regional water company
Aquacaras SA involves a 2.26 million-euro ($2.9 million
investment through 2015, Eptisa said in a statement. The group
currently supervises and manages project contracts in 13
counties across Romania, Eptisa said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
